Look at the little bump who is our daughter (we didn’t know she would be a she) 💖 who is now turning into such a mini human at 8 months old.  This time last year we were living in our Chorlton flat, still in our couples bubble and not REALLY knowing how much life will change for us.😉 As first time parents especially, we knew life as we knew it would change, we were prepared (as much as you can be) and expected all of the changes (again as much as you can). We were prepping our lives to becoming parents months before being pregnant. We went out to Lisbon and had the time of our lives as we knew it would probably be the last holiday pre pregnancy and baby! As soon as we got back I was on the folic acid and we were reading baby books 🤪  We knew we were going to have a baby in the near future, we were ready! One massive thing you learn is you never really know how much is going to change until you’re in that moment holding your baby when they’ve been born. When you’re pregnant you’re still in your couple bubble. I was really incredibly lucky to have a pretty smooth pregnancy. We continued to go out for meals, go to the cinema, go to the gym and basically leave the house without having to think. 👍  As SOON AS the baby arrives that is all flipped on it’s head upside down into another realm. Your relationship dynamics change (more on that another time). You never leave the house the same way EVER AGAIN! You think about 20 things all at once; what’s the weather doing? Need the nappy bag. Don’t forget the blanket! What food do we have? Oh I didn’t put a coat on. Did I change out of my slippers into shoes? Where is the little flopsy bunny rattle thing? Have I put pants on?!😅 This is probably changes and adapts to children’s ages until you’re probably in your 60s when all the babies have grown up. 😬  Being a parent is a real change and it is hard and challenging sometimes if not always. I don’t think that will change even after having the second, third, fourth etc babies (however many one may wish for). Yet I really wouldn’t have it any other way as her smiles and giggles are worth it ❤️
